SIMPLE: identify
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Identify
<hw>I*den"ti*fy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Identified</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Identifying</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>identifier</ets>. See <er>Identity</er>, and <er>-fy</er>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>To make to be the same; to unite or combine in such a
manner as to make one; to treat as being one or having the same purpose
or effect; to consider as the same in any relation.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Every precaution is taken to <qex>identify</qex> the interests of
the people and of the rulers.</q> <rj><qau>D. Ramsay.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Let us <qex>identify</qex>, let us incorporate ourselves with the
people.</q> <rj><qau>Burke.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To establish the identity of; to prove to be the
same with something described, claimed, or asserted; <as>as, to
<ex>identify</ex> stolen property</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Identify</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Identify
<hw>I*den"ti*fy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To
become the same; to coalesce in interest, purpose, use, effect,
etc.</def> <mark>[Obs. or R.]</mark></p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To coalesce in interest, purpose, use, effect, etc.;
to associate oneself in name, goals, or feelings; usually used with
<ptcl>with</ptcl>; <as>as, he <ex>identified</ex> with the grief she
felt at her father's death</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><q>An enlightened self-interest, which, when well understood, they
tell us will <qex>identify</qex> with an interest more enlarged and
public.</q> <rj><qau>Burke.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>identifying</ent>⟦br⟧
